@markekraus Thanks!

>serialize differently between ASP.NET and PowerShell

What does ASP.NET use? Newtonsoft?

@markekraus I agree this is a super breaking change so I'm not sure the best way to address it and I did make a hacked version of this that bypasses the ProcessCustomObject to produce the dictionary for particular types of objects. This alleviates the depth issue for me but isn't a good fix for PowerShell proper. 

I think it would be a little weird to have totally separate cmdlets that do the same thing with different underlying technology but idk if adding parameters to the existing cmdlets is the best option either. 

It's a tricky situation, I guess.
